	<h1>Errorception's script snippet</h1>
	<p>Here's a sample of the Errorception script tag:</p>
	<pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;!-- Sample code. Don't use this! Use the snippet in your settings instead. --&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
    (function(_,e,rr,s){_._errs=[s];var c=_.onerror;_.onerror=function(){var a=arguments;_errs.push(a);
    c&&c.apply(this,a)};var b=function(){var c=e.createElement(rr),b=e.getElementsByTagName(rr)[0];
    c.src="//beacon.errorception.com/"+s+".js";c.async=!0;b.parentNode.insertBefore(c,b)};
    _.addEventListener?_.addEventListener("load",b,!1):_.attachEvent("onload",b)})
    (window,document,"script","your-project-id");
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>
	<p>Don't worry, this script tag will not affect your page's performance at all. Yes, <strong>zero performance hit</strong>!</p>
